This paper deals with the problem of leader election in anonymous trees, which is a topic in distributed computing. The paper discusses tradeoffs between time and information, which suggests that it belongs to the categories of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Information Theory (cs.IT), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), and Algorithms (cs.AL). Among these categories, cs.DC and cs.DS are the most likely categories as they directly relate to the problem of leader election in distributed systems and the algorithms used to solve it. cs.IT is also likely as the paper discusses the amount of information required for the algorithm. cs.SI and cs.AL are less likely but still possible as they both deal with network-related problems and algorithms.
